mkrboot (0.4) unstable; urgency=low

  * new Maintainer (old: Christoph Lameter <clameter@debian.org>)
  * added /usr/lib/mkrboot/lilo.conf file (bug#4966)
  * this is a quick bugfix of the new maintainer, I have not looked at the
    code at all
  * fdos, syslinux, lilo, loadlin is only suggested now, dont depend on it
  * sanity check for missing lilo, fdos, syslinux, loadlin
    (THIS IS STILL OVERWRITING ANY PRESENT DISK w/o WARNING)

