mkrboot (0.3) unstable; urgency=low

  * created separate directories for the boot methods.
  * Included syslinux method and extrapolated what syslinux will do when
    finished
  * included contents of the old boot disks for debian
  * More fixes

 -- Christoph Lameter <clameter@debian.org>  Sat, 5 Oct 1996 09:00:00 -0800

mkrboot (0.2) unstable; urgency=low

  * A huge number of bugs fixed
  * Kernel boot method made dynamic according to kernel size
  * Diagnostic output as to how much space is sill available on
    the bootdisks.

